15.1.2 Numerical Stability Trick 
A big problem with doing inference in HMMâ€™s is the amount of multiplication of values 
<< 1, which makes it so that t and t can easily go to 1e âˆ’ 100. This is bad as it can 
underflow. There are 2 tricks that can be used in order to avoid this. 

